OL,3,CWhat's the difference between whooping
OL,4,Ccough and a normal cough?
OL,6,F"The reason why we see respiratory
OL,7,Finfections during the winter is that
OL,8,Fpeople will cluster indoors. If it's
OL,9,Fcold and wet, if you're indoors with
OL,10,Flittle ventilation, the window shut,
OL,11,Fthen there's many opportunities for
OL,12,Fthat bacteria to spread," he said.
OL,14,FHow is it treated?
OL,16,FThose with severe whooping cough, or
OL,17,Fbabies under 6 months with the
OL,18,Fillness, will need hospital treatment.
OL,19,FIt is treated with antibiotics.
OL,21,FHow contagious is it?
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G11/16
