OL,3,CWhat's the difference between whooping
OL,4,Ccough and a normal cough?
OL,6,FPeople with whooping cough are
OL,7,Fcontagious from about six days after
OL,8,Fthe start of cold-like symptoms to
OL,9,Fthree weeks after the coughing starts.
OL,11,FStarting antibiotics within three
OL,12,Fweeks of starting to cough can reduce
OL,13,Fthe time someone is contagious for.
OL,15,FDr Head explained whooping cough is
OL,16,Fabout as contagious as measles, which
OL,17,Fis one of the most infectious diseases
OL,18,Faround.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G12/16
