OL,3,CWhat's the difference between whooping
OL,4,Ccough and a normal cough?
OL,6,F"It has an R number of 15 to 17, so
OL,7,Fone infected person can potentially
OL,8,Finfect 15 to 17 other separable
OL,9,Fpeople," he said.
OL,11,F"It's also mostly in the upper
OL,12,Frespiratory tract meaning it is easier
OL,13,Fto spread because the bacteria are
OL,14,Fnearer the the the mouth and nose."
OL,16,FIs there a vaccine?
