OL,3,CWhat's the difference between whooping
OL,4,Ccough and a normal cough?
OL,6,FAll babies are offered a whooping
OL,7,Fcough vaccination as part of routine
OL,8,FNHS vaccines. It is given as part of
OL,9,Fthe six-in-one vaccine for babies at
OL,10,Feight, 12, and 16 weeks old.
OL,12,FIt's also administered in the four-in-
OL,13,Fone pre-school booster, for children
OL,14,Faged three years and four months old.
OL,16,FThe NHS recommends all pregnant women
OL,17,Fare vaccinated against whooping cough
OL,18,Fbetween 16 and 32 weeks.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G14/16
